Hong Kong Stocks Close Higher
HONG KONG , February 27 ( Xinhua ) -- Hong Kong stocks Friday surged for the third consecutive day to push the benchmark index to its highest since December 9 last year .
The key Hang Seng Index soared 255.91 points , or 2.28 percent , to close at the day 's high of 11,480.69 Friday .
The 33-blue chip index jumped 338.04 points , or 3.1 percent Thursday following a two-percent rally Wednesday .
It has gained nearly 800 points over the last three trading sessions .
Stocks had all-round increase in banking , property , utility , commercial and industrial sectors Friday .
Turnover was 13,547 million HK dollars ( 1,737 million U.S. dollars ) .
H shares were the biggest advancer during the week , with the Hang Seng China Enterprises Index jumping 15 percent to end at 719.28 points Friday .
Red chips , namely , China-affiliated corporations , also posted a rise of around 14 percent in the week .
